BORDER_COLOR: #C8C1B8
BORDER_STRONG: #87562E
FONT_HEADING: 'Frank Ruhl Libre', 'Times New Roman', David, serif
FONT_BODY: 'Heebo', 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, sans-serif
RADIUS_PX: 8px
SHADOW: 0 2px 12px rgba(135, 86, 46, 0.08)
SHADOW_HOVER: 0 4px 20px rgba(135, 86, 46, 0.15)
SPACING: airy

CRITICAL RESPONSIVE FRAMEWORK:
You MUST use these breakpoints:
- Mobile Small: max-width 375px
- Mobile Large: max-width 480px
- Tablet: max-width 768px
- Desktop Small: max-width 1024px
- Desktop Large: max-width 1440px
- Desktop XL: min-width 1441px

RESPONSIVE UNIT RULES:
- Use clamp() for all font sizes: clamp(min, preferred, max)
- Use percentage or vw for widths, NEVER fixed px for containers
- Use rem/em for spacing, not fixed px
- Images MUST use: max-width: 100%; height: auto; object-fit: cover;

WORDPRESS SAFETY RULES (MANDATORY):
- ALL CSS must be in a SINGLE <style> block at the top of the article element OR inline on each element.
- NEVER rely on Tailwind JIT, CDN bundlers, or external build steps.
- NEVER add <link rel="stylesheet"> tags pointing to external CSS files.
- NEVER use ES modules, build-time transforms, or admin-panel-only JS APIs.
- All interactive behavior MUST degrade gracefully without JavaScript (use <details>/<summary> for TOC & FAQ).
- Any required JavaScript must be a tiny inline <script> that works in the WordPress post body area (no WP admin dependencies).

The article MUST begin with a style block inside the article element. The article MUST start like this:

<article id="article-top" lang="he" dir="rtl">
<style>
@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Heebo:wght@300;400;500;600;700;800&family=Frank+Ruhl+Libre:wght@400;500;700;900&display=swap');
